  "text": "## OpenTelemetry Span Patterns Across Prometheus and Grafana\n\n### Tracer Initialization\n\nBoth projects initialize tracers globally using `otel.Tracer()` with an instrumentation scope string:\n- **Prometheus** (`prometheus/prometheus`): Uses `otel.Tracer(\"\")` with empty scope in rules/group.go:515, promql/engine.go:1919, scrape/scrape.go:748, storage/remote/client.go:290-402, and util/stats/query_stats.go:199\n- **Grafana** (`grafana/grafana`): Uses `otel.Tracer()` with package-specific scopes like `\"github.com/grafana/grafana/pkg/api\"` in pkg/api/api.go:59, `\"github.com/grafana/grafana/pkg/services/live\"` in pkg/services/live/live.go:61, `\"github.com/grafana/grafana/pkg/services/search\"` in pkg/services/search/service.go:21, and many others\n\n### Span Start/End Patterns\n\n**Prometheus** (prometheus/prometheus):\n- rules/group.go:515-518: `ctx, sp := otel.Tracer(\"\").Start(ctx, \"rule\")` with `defer sp.End()`\n- promql/engine.go:1919-1920: `ctx, span := otel.Tracer(\"\").Start(ctx, stats.InnerEvalTime.SpanOperation()+\" eval \"+reflect.TypeOf(expr).String())` with `defer span.End()`\n- scrape/scrape.go:748: `ctx, span := otel.Tracer(\"\").Start(ctx, \"Scrape\", trace.WithSpanKind(trace.SpanKindClient))` with `defer span.End()`\n- storage/remote/client.go:290: `ctx, span := otel.Tracer(\"\").Start(ctx, \"Remote Store\", trace.WithSpanKind(trace.SpanKindClient))`\n- storage/remote/queue_manager.go:2298: `ctx, span := otel.Tracer(\"\").Start(ctx, \"Remote Send Batch\")` with attribute setting\n- util/stats/query_stats.go:199: `ctx, span := otel.Tracer(\"\").Start(ctx, operation)` wrapped in SpanTimer struct\n\n**Grafana** (grafana/grafana):\n- pkg/api/quota.go:50: `ctx, span := hs.tracer.Start(c.Req.Context(), \"api.getOrgQuotasHelper\")` with `defer span.End()`\n- pkg/api/dashboard.go:87: `ctx, span := tracer.Start(c.Req.Context(), \"api.GetDashboard\")`\n- pkg/bus/bus.go:55: `_, span := b.tracer.Start(ctx, \"bus - \"+msgName)` with `defer span.End()`\n- pkg/expr/graph.go:127: `c, span := s.tracer.Start(c, \"SSE.ExecuteNode\")` with `defer span.End()`\n- pkg/expr/nodes.go:261: `ctx, span := s.tracer.Start(ctx, \"SSE.ExecuteDatasourceQuery\")`\n- pkg/expr/hysteresis.go:40: `traceCtx, span := tracer.Start(ctx, \"SSE.ExecuteHysteresis\")` with `defer span.End()`\n- pkg/tsdb/loki/loki.go:212: `ctx, span := tracer.Start(ctx, \"datasource.loki.queryData.runQueries\", trace.WithAttributes(...))`\n\n### Span Attribute Setting\n\n**Prometheus** patterns:\n- rules/group.go:516: `sp.SetAttributes(attribute.String(\"name\", rule.Name()))`\n- promql/engine.go:1922: `span.SetAttributes(attribute.String(\"operation\", ss.ShortString()))`\n- promql/engine.go:2328: `span.SetAttributes(attribute.Float64(\"value\", e.Val))`\n- storage/remote/queue_manager.go:2299-2310: Multiple `span.SetAttributes()` calls with Int, String attributes for request_size, samples, try, remote_name, remote_url, exemplars, histograms\n\n**Grafana** patterns:\n- pkg/bus/bus.go:58: `span.SetAttributes(attribute.String(\"msg\", msgName))`\n- pkg/expr/graph.go:128: `span.SetAttributes(attribute.String(\"node.refId\", node.RefID()))`\n- pkg/expr/graph.go:131: `span.SetAttributes(attribute.StringSlice(\"node.inputRefIDs\", inputRefIDs))`\n- pkg/expr/nodes.go:270-272: `span.SetAttributes(attribute.String(\"datasource.type\", firstNode.datasource.Type), attribute.String(\"datasource.uid\", firstNode.datasource.UID))`\n- pkg/expr/hysteresis.go:41-42: `span.SetAttributes(attribute.Int(\"previousLoadedDimensions\", len(h.LoadedDimensions)))` and `span.SetAttributes(attribute.Int(\"totalDimensions\", len(results.Values)))`\n- pkg/tsdb/loki/loki.go:212-214: `span.SetAttributes(attribute.Bool(\"runInParallel\", runInParallel), attribute.Int(\"queriesLength\", len(queries)))`\n- pkg/infra/tracing/tracing.go:437: `trace.WithAttributes(attributes...)` for setting attributes at span creation\n\n### Span Error Recording and Status Setting\n\n**Prometheus** (prometheus/prometheus):\n- rules/group.go:537: `sp.SetStatus(codes.Error, err.Error())`\n- storage/remote/queue_manager.go:621: `span.RecordError(err)`\n\n**Grafana** (grafana/grafana) - comprehensive error handling:\n- pkg/modules/tracing/listener.go:92-97: `l.stateSpan.SetStatus(codes.Error, err.Error())` and `l.stateSpan.RecordError(err)` with conditional status setting\n- pkg/infra/tracing/tracing.go:415-424: `Error()` function sets both status and records error: `span.SetStatus(codes.Error, err.Error())` and `span.RecordError(err, trace.WithAttributes(attr...))`\n- pkg/expr/nodes.go:297: `span.SetStatus(codes.Error, \"failed to query data source\")` and `span.RecordError(e)`\n- pkg/expr/graph.go:214-216: Error handling with `span.RecordError(err)` and `span.SetStatus(codes.Error, err.Error())`\n- pkg/tsdb/loki/api.go:231-233: `span.RecordError(res.Error)` and `span.SetStatus(codes.Error, res.Error.Error())`\n- pkg/modules/tracing/listener.go:108-114: `span.SetAttributes(attribute.String(...))` before error recording\n\n### Advanced Span Configuration\n\n**Span Kind Configuration**:\n- prometheus/prometheus - scrape/scrape.go:748: `trace.WithSpanKind(trace.SpanKindClient)`\n- prometheus/prometheus - storage/remote/client.go:290, 402: `trace.WithSpanKind(trace.SpanKindClient)`\n- grafana/grafana - pkg/middleware/request_tracing.go:111: `trace.WithSpanKind(trace.SpanKindServer)`\n- grafana/grafana - pkg/infra/httpclient/httpclientprovider/tracing_middleware.go:28: `trace.WithSpanKind(trace.SpanKindClient)`\n\n**Attributes at Span Creation**:\n- grafana/grafana - pkg/tsdb/loki/loki.go:131-132: `trace.WithAttributes(attribute.String(\"url\", lokiURL))`\n- grafana/grafana - pkg/services/team/teamimpl/team.go:42: `trace.WithAttributes(attribute.Int64(\"orgID\", cmd.OrgID))`\n- grafana/grafana - pkg/storage/secret/encryption/data_key_store.go:42: `trace.WithAttributes(attribute.String(\"namespace\", namespace))`\n\n**Span Events**:\n- prometheus/prometheus - promql/engine.go:1101-1109: `span.AddEvent(\"expand start\", trace.WithAttributes(attribute.String(...)))` and `span.AddEvent(\"expand end\", trace.WithAttributes(attribute.Int(...)))`\n- grafana/grafana - pkg/storage/unified/sql/rvmanager/rv_manager.go:334: `span.AddEvent(\"save_rv_failed\", trace.WithAttributes(...))`\n\n### Summary\n\nBoth prometheus/prometheus and grafana/grafana use OpenTelemetry spans extensively with the following consistent patterns:\n1. Global tracer initialization using `otel.Tracer()` with optional instrumentation scope\n2. Span creation with `tracer.Start(ctx, spanName)` and defer cleanup with `span.End()`\n3. Attribute setting via `span.SetAttributes()` with typed attribute constructors (String, Int, Bool, StringSlice, etc.)\n4. Optional attributes set at span creation time using `trace.WithAttributes()`\n5. Error handling via `span.RecordError()` combined with `span.SetStatus(codes.Error, message)`\n6. Span kind configuration for client/server operations using `trace.WithSpanKind()`\n7. Event recording with `span.AddEvent()` for detailed operation tracking\n8. Helper functions and patterns for error recording with context preservation\n\nGrafana has more extensive use of OpenTelemetry across services with centralized tracer initialization per service, while Prometheus uses minimal scope specification with global tracing focused on critical operations."
